Feel the rhythm of the rain,
As drops dance on the windowpane.
Every splash a call, a playful song,
In nature’s beauty, we all belong.

Listen to the rustling leaves,
The stories carried in the breeze.
With every heartbeat, life anew,
In nature’s grace, we find our view.

— Zora Neale Hurston

- Zora Neale Hurston
